-- Kuwait's KIPCO says receives approval for stake increase in Burgan Bank
-- By Azza Al Arabi
-- Thu Sep 04, 2014 04:24AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Sept 4 (Reuters) - Kuwait Projects Company <KPRO.KW> (KIPCO) said on Thursday it received approval from the country's central bank to increase its stake in Burgan Bank <BURG.KW> by 5 percent.

A bourse filing by KIPCO added that its direct and indirect stake in the Kuwait's third-largest lender by assets currently stands at 57.94 percent.